GUILTY plea entered to count 1, OWI - 5th.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2 through 6.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Pay a $1,500.00 ($750 X 2) fine plus costs, total of $2,908.00.  The Court will order that the $220.00 assessment fee be deducted from the OWI surcharge.  The court further orders that the $500.00 cash bail be applied to the fine and costs for a balance owing of $2,188.00;
2) Undergo the Intoxicated Driver assessment and Driver Safety Plan;
3) Spend nine (9) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing immediately;
4) Provide a DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) maintain fulltime employment or work search;
7) maintain absolute sobriety.
In addition, the Court orders a thirty-six (36) month DL revocation and period of Ignition Interlock.
The defendant has credit for 2 days.
Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights.
Assessment order.
Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
Minutes.
